# mlx-forge

**The M-series local inference optimizer & memory manager**

CLI and background daemon for monitoring and optimizing Apple Silicon (M1–M4) resources during local AI workloads. Prevents OOMs, manages Metal cache, and provides a terminal dashboard for Unified Memory.

Part of Project Maclawd (MacBook bot). See `docs/project-maclawd.md` in the repo.

## Install

From repo root:

```bash
cd mlx-forge
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate   # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -e .
```

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|--------|--------------|
| `forge top` | Real-time Unified Memory & Metal cache dashboard |
| `forge sweep` | Force-clear MLX Metal cache and Python GC |
| `forge smash <hf-repo-id> [--bits 4] [--out-dir DIR]` | Convert and quantize a HuggingFace model to MLX (requires `pip install mlx-lm`) |
| `forge run <model-path> [--prompt "…"] [--guard-thermals]` | Run an MLX model; `--guard-thermals` uses chunked generation with pauses to reduce thermal load |

## Quick start

```bash
# Free Metal cache between heavy runs (use after Workhorse, before next task)
forge sweep

# Watch memory while a model is loading or generating
forge top
```

## Requirements

- macOS with Apple Silicon
- Python 3.10+
- MLX (`pip install mlx`)
- For `forge smash` and `forge run`: `pip install mlx-lm` (or `pip install -e ".[smash]"`)

## Dev: tests and lint

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
pytest tests/ -v
ruff check src/ tests/
```
